    h1 Theme Based Rendering
    p When we develop Framework7 app for multiple platforms with mutliple themes (<code>ios</code>, <code>md</code>, <code>aurora</code>) we need to control which elements will appear for one or another theme, like showing different icon for iOS and MD themes.
    p There are special classes that allow to control this:
    ul
      li <code>if-ios</code> - element will be rendered only for iOS theme
      li <code>if-not-ios</code> - element will be removed/hidden for theme other than iOS
      li <code>if-md</code> - element will be rendered only for MD theme
      li <code>if-not-md</code> - element will be removed/hidden for theme other than MD
      li <code>if-aurora</code> - element will be rendered only for Aurora theme
      li <code>if-not-aurora</code> - element will be removed/hidden for theme other than Aurora
    p This is, for example how we hide Navbar's back button text for MD theme:
    :code(lang="html")
      <div class="navbar">
        <div class="navbar-inner sliding">
          <div class="left">
            <a href="#" class="link back">
              <i class="icon icon-back"></i>
              <!-- back button text will be visible only in iOS and Aurora themes -->
              <span class="if-not-md">Back</span>
            </a>
          </div>
          ...
        </div>
      </div>
